            "answer_text": "Hello, When it comes to stock share prices, points and dollars are interchangeable. If a stock lost three points, it lost three dollars per share. If the stock gained three points, its share rose by three dollars. That\u2019s where percentages also come in. If a stock rises four points from $8 to $12, it went up 33 percent. However, if a high-priced stock rises from $100 to $103, it has gained just 3 percent. Hope it will help. ",
